# Liahona.AI Runtime

## Runtime Philosophy

Runtime systems exist to deliver the experience, not define ultimate meaning.

Implementation should support:
- orientation
- continuity
- clarity
- restraint
- grounded interaction

Avoid feature sprawl and unnecessary complexity.

## Runtime Responsibilities

Runtime systems may include:
- interaction logic
- rendering systems
- UI state
- navigation systems
- semantic retrieval
- memory systems
- deployment/runtime behavior
- continuity projection

## Layer Visibility

Functions and systems should make their ontological role visible when useful.

Examples:

- Canonical
- Interpretive
- Runtime
- Projection
- Continuity

Comments and architecture should preserve clarity between layers.

## Behavioral Alignment

Runtime behavior should remain aligned with:
- governance principles
- source boundaries
- continuity philosophy
- restrained interaction

Implementation should not drift into:
- artificial engagement systems
- manipulative interaction loops
- fake emotional intelligence
- excessive abstraction
- pseudo-spiritual authority

## Operational Direction

Prefer:
- modular systems
- semantic organization
- readable architecture
- composable components
- portable continuity

Reduce:
- hidden complexity
- prompt dependency
- giant monolithic context
- unnecessary runtime clutter